Sri Lanka Approves 28.2 Million Pound HSBC Loan to Build Bridges

-- B y   A n u s h a   O n d a a t j i e   a n d   A s a n t h a   S i r i m a n n e
-- 
2011-10-20T06:42:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-20/sri-lanka-approves-28-2-million-pound-hsbc-loan-to-build-bridges.html
Sri Lanka ’s cabinet approved a 28.2
million pound credit agreement with  HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA)  to build
steel bridges on the island, spokesman Keheliya Rambukwella said
in  Colombo  today.  Sri Lanka’s state-run People’s Bank will also lend the
government 6.8 million pounds for the project to be built by
Cleveland Bridge UK Ltd., he said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
